(1. Executive Summary) Tj
/F1 8.4 Tf
1 0 0 1 46.00 635.00 Tm
(ForesightX is a cinematic decision simulation platform that helps a user explore the possible) Tj
/F1 8.4 Tf
1 0 0 1 46.00 624.90 Tm
(consequences of an important choice before acting. The user enters a current situation, a) Tj
/F1 8.4 Tf
1 0 0 1 46.00 614.80 Tm
(decision under consideration, and a domain. The system then produces three future timelines:) Tj
/F1 8.4 Tf
1 0 0 1 46.00 604.70 Tm
(optimistic, realistic, and pessimistic. Each timeline includes a probability, milestones, final) Tj
/F1 8.4 Tf
1 0 0 1 46.00 594.60 Tm
(state, and actionable factors.) Tj
/F1 8.4 Tf
1 0 0 1 46.00 580.50 Tm
(The product is designed for hackathon judging and live demonstration. Its primary value is) Tj
/F1 8.4 Tf
1 0 0 1 46.00 570.40 Tm
(clarity under uncertainty. Instead of presenting a static answer, ForesightX shows a visible) Tj
/F1 8.4 Tf
1 0 0 1 46.00 560.30 Tm
(reasoning pipeline, streams progress in real time, and gives users tools to interrogate each) Tj
/F1 8.4 Tf
1 0 0 1 46.00 550.20 Tm
(future branch after the simulation completes.) Tj
/F1 8.4 Tf
1 0 0 1 46.00 536.10 Tm
(Version 2 expands the original working system with follow-up analysis, milestone drill-down,) Tj
/F1 8.4 Tf
1 0 0 1 46.00 526.00 Tm
(what-if reruns, shareable result cards, a refined responsive layout, and improved deployment) Tj
